error[E0499]: cannot borrow `stream` as mutable more than once at a time
  --> tests/compile_fail/stream_double_next_borrow.rs:51:18
   |
49 |     let env = stream.next().await.unwrap().unwrap();
   |               ------ first mutable borrow occurs here
50 |     // Holding `env` here aliases the cursor — calling `next()` again must fail.
51 |     let _again = stream.next().await;
   |                  ^^^^^^ second mutable borrow occurs here
52 |     // Use `env` after the second `next()` to force the borrow to overlap.
53 |     let _ = env.payload();
   |             --- first borrow later used here
